<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5859] Don&apos;t return internal StreamState objects from streaming mbeans</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5859</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The stream manager mbean returns StreamState objects. We want to avoid returning internal C* objects over jmx. We should switch to a map or something similar that can represent streaming state.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12662499">CASSANDRA-5859</key>
            <summary>Don&apos;t return internal StreamState objects from streaming mbeans</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
